SUMMARY:A Conversation with Clark Aboud\, Composer for Video Games & Film
DESCRIPTION:Students\, sign up here &gt\;Clark Aboud is a composer and pr
 oducer with a fascination for all styles and sounds. That love for a rang
 e of genres finds its way into all of Clark's music\, whether blending om
 inous orchestral colors with unique synths in the hit indie game Slay the
  Spire\, in the mix of sampling\, lo-fi synths &amp\; beats for the BAFTA
  winning Kind Words (lo fi chill beats to write to)\, or bringing retro-c
 onsole synthsand ambience to the critically acclaimed VIDEOVERSE.Alongsid
 e writing for short films and animation\, Clark has contributed to a shor
 t for HBO's Sesame Street\, and provided underscore for programs on VICE\
 , NBC\, MTV\, Discovery\, Animal Planet\, Bravo &amp\; others.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW161449428 
