BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260326T160000Z
DTEND:20260326T170000Z
LOCATION:LOWELL E. BAIER HALL/IU MAURER SCHOOL OF LAW - Room Number: 123
GEO:39.165074;-86.526424
SUMMARY:A Conversation on Legal Trends in Music & AI with Dan Amin and Ro
 bert Meitus
DESCRIPTION:The Indiana University Maurer School of Law is pleased to par
 ticipate once again in AlgoRhythms 2026\, the third annual conference pre
 sented in collaboration with the Indiana University Jacobs School of Musi
 c exploring the intersection of music and artificial intelligence.  As a 
 part of the larger program\, Maurer will host a featured conversation tit
 led A Conversation on Legal Trends in Music &amp\; AI. For this conversat
 ion\, we are delighted to welcome Dan Amin '06\, Assistant Chief Counsel 
 at Lucasfilm. Mr. Amin will be joined by Robert Meitus\, Partner at Meitu
 s Strohm and Maurer Adjunct Professor.Dan Amin (Assistant Chief Counsel\,
  Lucasfilm)  Dan oversees legal support for Lucasfilm's technology initia
 tives and leads legal and business affairs for Industrial Light &amp\; Ma
 gic (ILM)\, ILMxLAB\, Skywalker Sound\, and Technoprops. Since joining in
  2014\, he has guided ILM's global expansion\, including the launch of st
 udios in Australia and India and the development of StageCraft virtual pr
 oduction services. A founding leadership team member of ILMxLAB\, he serv
 es as primary counsel for its AR\, VR\, and immersive projects. Previousl
 y\, Dan was in-house counsel at PBS\, managing technology transactions an
 d regulatory matters\, and co-authoring the Supreme Court amicus brief in
  FCC v. Fox (2012). He holds degrees from Carnegie Mellon and Indiana Uni
 versity Maurer School of Law.  See a Full schedule of AlgoRhythm events h
 ere: https://blogs.iu.edu/jsominnovation/algorhythms-the-world-of-music-a
 nd-ai/ (https://blogs.iu.edu/jsominnovation/algorhythms-the-world-of-musi
 c-and-ai/)  Sign up to attend: https://forms.office.com/r/4QgGSdDfzp (htt
 ps://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fforms.offi
 ce.com%2Fr%2F4QgGSdDfzp&amp\;data=05%7C02%7Clawrooms%40iu.edu%7C8b6a058bd
 1c34953a71b08de756a77de%7C1113be34aed14d00ab4bcdd02510be91%7C1%7C0%7C6390
 77297324940997%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLj
 AuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&a
 mp\;sdata=HnoaNgpgT3GEgAh93kCPUBxACwthBA0nAYIWALmjz7k%3D&amp\;reserved=0)
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  The Indiana University Maurer School of
  Law is pleased to participate once again in AlgoRhythms 2026\, the third
  annual conference presented in collaboration with the Indiana University
  Jacobs School of Music exploring the intersection of music and artificia
 l intelligence.</p><p>  As a part of the larger program\, Maurer will hos
 t a featured conversation titled <strong><em>A Conversation on Legal Tren
 ds in Music &amp\; AI</em></strong>. For this conversation\, we are delig
 hted to welcome <strong>Dan Amin</strong> '06\, Assistant Chief Counsel a
 t Lucasfilm. Mr. Amin will be joined by Robert Meitus\, Partner at Meitus
  Strohm and Maurer Adjunct Professor.</p><p><strong>Dan Amin (Assistant C
 hief Counsel\, Lucasfilm)</strong><br />  Dan oversees legal support for 
 Lucasfilm's technology initiatives and leads legal and business affairs f
 or Industrial Light &amp\; Magic (ILM)\, ILMxLAB\, Skywalker Sound\, and 
 Technoprops. Since joining in 2014\, he has guided ILM's global expansion
 \, including the launch of studios in Australia and India and the develop
 ment of StageCraft virtual production services. A founding leadership tea
 m member of ILMxLAB\, he serves as primary counsel for its AR\, VR\, and 
 immersive projects. Previously\, Dan was in-house counsel at PBS\, managi
 ng technology transactions and regulatory matters\, and co-authoring the 
 Supreme Court amicus brief in <em>FCC v. Fox</em> (2012). He holds degree
 s from Carnegie Mellon and Indiana University Maurer School of Law.</p><p
 >  See a Full schedule of AlgoRhythm events here: <a href="https://blogs.
 iu.edu/jsominnovation/algorhythms-the-world-of-music-and-ai/">https://blo
 gs.iu.edu/jsominnovation/algorhythms-the-world-of-music-and-ai/</a></p><p
 >  Sign up to attend: <a href="https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook
 .com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fforms.office.com%2Fr%2F4QgGSdDfzp&amp\;data=05%7C
 02%7Clawrooms%40iu.edu%7C8b6a058bd1c34953a71b08de756a77de%7C1113be34aed14
 d00ab4bcdd02510be91%7C1%7C0%7C639077297324940997%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8
