  Maddux (beatBread)    - Ethan Castro (EDGE Sound)    - Joe Berman (SongH
 ub)    - Olivia Jones (MIDiA Research)12:15 p.m.Keynote AddressDmitri Vie
 tze (Founder\, RPS and Music Tectonics)2:00 p.m.Creativity in AI: Artisti
 c Migration &amp\; New TerritoriesModerated by Ed Dallis-Comentale (Asst\
 , VP for Research in Arts &amp\; Humanities\, Indiana University)    - Ca
 leb Weintraub (Eskenazi School\, IU)    - Ivica Bukvic (KIX Lab\, IU)    
 - Raina Murnak (U Miami)    - Jason Palamara (IU Indianapolis)4:00 p.m.Cr
 eativity in AI: Understanding The Known &amp\; UnknownModerator: Marcus L
 awrence (Zinstrel)    - Tom Collins (U Miami)    - Tristra Newyear Yeager
  (Music Tectonics)    - Timirah James (Artist\, AI Music researcher)    -
 &#160\; Andy West (IU Jacobs School of Music)    The summit provides an o
 pportunity to wrestle with questions about authorship\, ownership\, envir
 onmental impact\, cultural disruption\, business transformation\, and the
  meaning of creativity itself.  Primary partners for this project are the
  Maurer School of Law\, IU Innovates\, Music Tectonics\, and the AI+Digit
 al Futures Team.  AlgoRhythms is generously supported by Frank Graves\, w
 hose contributions to the Jacobs School of Music and Indiana University a
 re deeply appreciated. Additional funding is made possible through the ge
 nerous support of the Office of the Vice President for Research in Arts &
 amp\; Humanities\, IU Innovates\, the Bloomington Office of the Chancello
 r\, the Maurer School of Law\, and Sweetwater Sound.
