 etana. The latter received the enthusiastic praise of <em>Fanfare Magazin
 e</em> ("you cannot afford to be without this ŌĆ” [it] may just be the be
 st of the best Brahms B Major Trio recordings"). Devoted to new music\, t
 he trio has commissioned ensemble and concerto works for trio from distin
 guished composers Lera Auerbach\, Paul Chihara\, Michael Gilbertson\, Mic
 hael Hersch\, and Paul Lansky\, and have recorded many of these along wit
 h others by American composers Fred Lerdahl\, Chen Yi\, Clancy Newman\, a
